      "message": "I think that property should not be published in the env file.   We are shooting for it to alway be enabled, but in the meantime while we reach maturity in the short time, I think we have to start with it disabled (it can be a source of additional problems besides the ones that naturally will arise interoperating with all other components).  What I propose we do here is: \n\n1. guard is disabled by default for the time being until we gain confidence in production environment, and we enable it.\n\n2. check the getEnvironmentProperty() - if the property exists just set it to its value, either true or false.\n\nThis will allow us:\n\n1.  Initially go with it disabled (until we are comfortable with it and tested against a PDP-X), so won\u0027t interfere those folks testing our delivery.\n\n2.  For us developers in labs, rackspace and others, we can do more integration testing to bless the functionality, we should be able to switch it on/off without restarting externally using the telemetry REST apis (ie. swagger, curl, etc ..), there are calls to set up environment variables.\n\nOnce we are satisfied with it, we will reverse the default here to guardEnabled\u003dtrue",
